Given a fixed limitTon the length of time social distancing / quarantines may be imposed, how should they be scheduled in order to minimize the total number of fatalities? Should the social distancing / quarantines be imposed in one contiguous interval, or broken up into multiple intervals? Should it be imposed early, when very few individuals are infected, or later when the infection levels are higher?To study this mathematically, we assume that a constant fraction of individuals who contract the disease will die.1 In this case, minimizing the total number of fatalities is equivalent to minimizing \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
